The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Tuesday, August 03, 2004 				 Woman back from dead
																								Purulia, Aug. 2: Buried in a ditch after being strangled by her husband, a woman returned from the dead last Saturday, days after she had been unceremoniously disposed of.																								Hemadibala, 24, married about six years ago to Ramesh Mahato of Hetgugui village, in Purulias Arsa district  about 270 km from Calcutta  was ill-treated by her husband and in-laws for not bearing any children. 																								On the night of July 28, during a quarrel, an angry Ramesh strangled his wife. Taking her to be dead, he and his parents buried her in a ditch, from where she was rescued by a villager on Friday.
